Creates a DataFrame from dictionary data and calculates mean values using Pandas data analysis library.

import pandas as pd

data = {
    "Name": ["Aman", "Ravi", "Priya"],
    "Marks": [85, 90, 88]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("DataFrame:")
print(df)

print("Mean Marks:", df["Marks"].mean())

OUTPUT-DataFrame:
    Name  Marks
0   Aman     85
1   Ravi     90
2  Priya     88
Mean Marks: 87.66666666666667
